Then the height of the trapezoid is
\[BE - AD = \frac{x}{2 \cos \theta} - \frac{x}{2 \sin \theta} = \frac{x \sin \theta - x \cos \theta}{2 \cos \theta \sin \theta} = \frac{x (\sin \theta - \cos \theta)}{2 \cos \theta \sin \theta}.\]Since $\sin \theta = 0.8,$ $\cos \theta = \sqrt{1 - \sin^2 \theta} = 0.6.$  Hence, the height of the trapezoid is
